Copyright 2026 Copyleft Cultivars Nonprofit and Caleb DeLeeuw

This product includes software originally developed as the EVEE MCP Server
at https://github.com/goodfire-ai/evee-mcp (Goodfire AI), which provided the
MCP server scaffolding, the @mcp.tool() decorator pattern, the FastMCP
transport conventions, the .claude/skills/ skill layout, and the SKILL.md
"Gotchas" documentation convention. The data semantics, the trait atlas, the
19-tool surface, and all integrations beyond Ensembl are entirely new in
this fork.

This product queries data from the following public databases. Each
preserves its own terms of use; users should respect them:

  - Ensembl Plants (Sanger / EMBL-EBI) — https://plants.ensembl.org/
  - UniProt (SIB / EMBL-EBI / PIR) — https://www.uniprot.org/
  - Europe PMC — https://europepmc.org/
  - STRING-db (SIB / EMBL) — https://string-db.org/
  - Medicinal Genomics Kannapedia — https://www.kannapedia.net/

We are grateful to the public-sector scientists, curators, and
infrastructure teams who maintain these resources. Tools that aggregate
their work are only useful because they make their data freely
accessible.

This product also references and links to (but does not redistribute
data from) Plant Reactome (Gramene), MaizeGDB (USDA), the 1001 Genomes
Project (Arabidopsis), the 3K Rice Genomes Project, and other community
plant-genomics resources.

This is part of the Copyleft Cultivars Nonprofit ecosystem alongside
TinyLLamaFarmer (offline natural-farming AI) and gemma4-natural-farming
(open-weight model fine-tuned on Korean Natural Farming and JADAM
literature). See https://github.com/CopyleftCultivars for sibling projects.

Plant genetics, like seeds, should circulate freely.
